      • addMotionStoppedHook

        public void addMotionStoppedHook(Consumer<MotionSprPrimitive> hook)
        Adds a hook that will be called when the motion associated with this primitive is stopped.

        Motion stopped means that:

      • motion stopped event received from the associated SPR, or
      • associated SPR is finished (normally, or canceled, or invalid) from active state

        Hooks are called synchronously in the state handling thread of the associated SPR and must not block or take too long

Parameters:
hook - hook that will be called when motion s stopped
